# Pizza 505 ENMU – Restaurant Booking & Ordering System

A full-stack **Java EE MVC web application** built for ENMU’s CS 472 Software Engineering course.  
The system enables administrators, staff, and customers to manage restaurant menus, reservations, and online orders in real time.


##  Overview

**Design Pattern:** Model-View-Controller (MVC)  
**Language:** Java (Servlet/JSP)  
**Server:** Apache Tomcat 7.0.109  
**Database:** H2 Embedded (File Mode)  
**Persistence:** JDBC  
**Email Service:** JavaMail API + Gmail SMTP  

## Libraries & Dependencies

| Library | Version | Purpose |
| **javax.servlet-api** | 3.0.1 | Provides Servlet/JSP interfaces for web layer |
| **javax.mail** | 1.6.2 | Used by `EmailUtil` for password reset / invite emails |
| **activation** | 1.1.1 | Required by JavaMail for MIME message handling |
| **h2** | 1.4.200 | Lightweight embedded SQL database (local `.mv.db` file) |
| **mysql-connector-java** | 5.1.49 | Optional external DB compatibility | **Can connect to MySQL 5.7+ by switching the connection string in DBConnection.java.**
| **JSTL (included in Tomcat)** | — | Simplifies JSP logic and loops |

> These libraries are stored in `/lib/` or linked through IntelliJ’s **Project Structure → Libraries**  

##  Running the Project

###  Option 1: Using IntelliJ IDEA (Build Artifact)
1. Open **IntelliJ IDEA Ultimate** (recommended)  
2. Import the project folder (`File → Open → Fall2025Project`)  
3. Go to **File → Project Structure → Artifacts → + Web Application: Exploded → From Modules**  
4. Choose output directory: `out/artifacts/Fall2025Project_war_exploded/`  
5. Configure **Tomcat 7.0.109** as your run server  
6. Run the artifact → open browser:  
    `http://localhost:8080/Fall2025Project/login.jsp`

Database
•	Uses H2 Embedded Database auto-initialized by DBConnection.java.
•	Database file stored at:
/data/restaurantdb.mv.db
Tables include:
•	users, staff, customers
•	MenuItem, Orders, OrderItems
•	reservations, password_reset_tokens
Default admin/staff/customer accounts are seeded automatically.

